Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setIoRowMargin(25.10)                                    setIoRowMargin(25.10)

Name
       setIoRowMargin  -  Sets  the distance from the die boundary edge to the
       I/O row starting edge location

Syntax
       setIoRowMargin

       [-help]

       side

       row

       margin

       Sets the distance from the die boundary edge to the  I/O  row  starting
       edge location. You can use this command for multiple I/O rows.

       Note:  You  can use the Edit I/O Ring form to specify I/O pad rings and
       row margins for multiple rows. Alternatively, to achieve the same using
       text commands, you must first use the setIoRowMargin command to set the
       distance from the die boundary edge to start of each row and  then  use
       the placePadIO command to place the I/O pads evenly between these rows.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each setIoRowMargin parameter.  For  a  detailed
              description  of  the  command and all of its parameters, use the
              man command:

              man setIoRowMargin

       <side> Specifies the side of the I/O row margin, where n is  the  North
              side, w is the West side, s is the South side, and e is the East
              side.

              Data_type: string, optional

       <margin>
              Specifies  the distance between the die boundary edge to the I/O
              row edge, in microns.

              Data_type: float, optional

       <row>  Specifies the I/O row number. This value can be up  to  8  rows.
              You  can  also use this value in conjunction with the placePadIO
              and placePIO -optIOs commands to specify the number of rows  for
              placing  peripheral  I/O  cells  for the CLASS PAD and CLASS PAD
              AREAIO flows respectively.

              * To create and optimize multiple I/O Rows in a CLASS PAD  flow,
                use the following commands:

                setIoRowMargin row

                placePadIO

              * To create and optimize multiple I/O Rows in a CLASS PAD AREAIO
                flow, use the following commands:

                setIoRowMargin rowNumber

                placePIO -optIOs

              Maximum: 1000

              Minimum: 0

              Data_type: int, optional

Example
       The  following command sets the North side of the second I/O row start-
       ing edge value at 300 microns from the die boundary edge to the  second
       I/O row edge:

       setIoRowMargin n 2 300

